{{Infobox football league season |competition=[[Venezuelan Primera División]] |season=[[1968 in Venezuelan football|1968]] |winners=[[Unión Deportiva Canarias|Canarias]] (1st title) |relegated= |continentalcup1= |continentalcup1 qualifiers= |continentalcup2= |continentalcup2 qualifiers= |matches= |total goals= |league topscorer= |biggest home win= |biggest away win= |highest scoring= |longest wins = |longest unbeaten = |longest losses = |highest attendance = |lowest attendance = |average attendance = |prevseason=[[1967 Venezuelan Primera División season|1967]] |nextseason=[[1969 Venezuelan Primera División season|1969]] }}
The '''1968 season of the [[Venezuelan Primera División]]''', the top category of [[Venezuela]]n football, was played by 6 teams. The national champions were [[Unión Deportiva Canarias|Canarias]].
