{{Infobox handball club| | clubname = Potaissa Turda | fullname = AHC Potaissa Turda | image = [[File:AHC_Potaissa_Turda_logo.png]] | short name = Potaissa | founded = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|2000}} | ground = | capacity = 650 | chairman = {{flagicon|ROU}} Flaviu Sâsâeac | manager = {{flagicon|ROU}} Horațiu Gal | assistent = {{flagicon|ROU}} Ovidiu Gal | league = [[Liga Națională (men's handball)|Liga Națională]] | season = [[2017–18 Liga Națională (men's handball)|2017–18]] | position = Liga Națională, 3rd | website = http://www.ahcpotaissa.ro/ | colour1 = yellow | colour2 = dodgerblue
| pattern_la1 = _bluelines | pattern_b1 = _2blueshoulderstripes | pattern_ra1 = _bluelines | pattern_sh1 = _yellow_stripes | leftarm1 = FFFF00 | body1 = FFFF00 | rightarm1 = FFFF00 | shorts1 = 0000FF
| pattern_la2 = | pattern_b2 = _2yellowshoulderstripes | pattern_ra2 = | pattern_sh2 = _yellow_stripes | leftarm2 = 0000FF | body2 = 0000FF | rightarm2 = 0000FF | shorts2 = 0000FF }}
'''AHC Potaissa Turda''' is a [[team handball|men's handball]] club from [[Turda]], [[Romania]], that plays in the [[Liga Națională (men's handball)|Romanian Handball League]]. Potaissa Turda is one of the most important Romanian teams in the last decade. In the last four years, is the only team that have qualified for the Final 4, in every season. Potaissa Turda won the EHF Challenge Cup in 2018, after a final against AEK Athens.
Turda was promoted to the first division in 2011, not long time after the club was near bankruptcy, in 2008. In those days, their players played just for joy and weekly training was just a dream they could talk about.
Potaissa Turda's fairytail story began back in 2007, when their home sports hall, from ''Gheorghe Baritiu'' school, was inaugurated and the team's amateur players could play finally in Turda. For example, one of the sqaud's member was the actual team president, ''Flaviu Constantin Sâsâeac'', who used to play for Turda, and also being the team president, since 2003.
Also an old member of the club is the coach, ''Horațiu Gal [http://www.ahcpotaissa.ro/Acasa/interviu-horatiu-gal-ma-simt-foarte-bine-aici-turda-este-casa-mea.html]'', being the head coach for almost ten years, after retiring from his player career, playing last time in Germany, for '''TSV Bad Salgau'''.
Another reason why Potaissa's early succes is not that surprising, can be that the club has more youth squads, around '''220 childrend and young players''' representing Turda in national competitions.[https://pressone.ro/uriasii-din-curtea-scolii/]
