{{Infobox KHL team | current = 2017-18 NL season | team = EV Zug | colour = #005DC6 | colour text = #FFFFFF | logo = [[File:EV Zug logo.svg|185px]] | name2 = '''EV Zug''' | nickname = EVZ | founded = 1967 | folded = | city = [[Zug]], [[Switzerland]] | arena = [[Bossard Arena]] | capacity = 7,200 | league = ''' [[National League (ice hockey)|National League]]''' | division = | conference = | uniform = | colours = Blue and white | owner = | gm = {{flagicon|SUI}} [[Patrick Lengwiler]] | coach = {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Dan Tangnes]] | captain = {{flagicon|SUI}} [[Raphael Diaz]] | honors = | affiliates = [[EV Zug Academy]] | website = [http://www.evz.ch/ www.evz.ch] }}
'''EV Zug''' is a professional men's [[ice hockey]] team from [[Zug]], [[Switzerland]]. It is a member of the [[National League (ice hockey)|National League]] and plays its home games at the [[Bossard Arena]].
==History== EV Zug won its lone championship in the 1997–98 season.
On October 3, 2011, the club defeated the [[New York Rangers]] of the [[National Hockey League|NHL]] by the score of 8-4 in an exhibition game.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/recap.htm?id=2011011004 | title=Rangers fall to Swiss squad, 8-4 | publisher=''NHL.com'' | last=Rosen | first=Dan | date=2011-10-03 | accessdate=2011-10-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nationalleague.ch/NL/aktuell/de/20111004_news_1.php | title=EV Zug wins against the New York Rangers! | language=German | publisher=''www.nationalleague.ch'' | date=2011-10-03 | accessdate=2011-10-03}}</ref> Former NHLer [[Josh Holden]], who at the time was suspended from the NLA, was permitted to play and scored twice. He and [[Fabian Schnyder]] each had three points and [[Esa Pirnes]] also had two goals. Former Ranger goaltender [[Jussi Markkanen]] had the win in net in front of a sellout crowd at [[Bossard Arena]].
