{{Infobox football biography | name = José Miguel Granadino | image = | fullname = José Miguel Granadino León | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|9|28}} | birth_place = [[Santa Ana, El Salvador|Santa Ana]], [[El Salvador]] | height = {{convert|1.80|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} | position = [[Defender (football)|Defender]] | currentclub = [[C.D. FAS|FAS]] | clubnumber = 6 | youthyears1 = 2001&ndash;2005 |youthclubs1 = Cuscachapa | years1 = 2005 |clubs1 = [[C.D. FAS|FAS]] reserves |caps1 = |goals1 = | years2 = 2006–2013 |clubs2 = [[C.D. FAS|FAS]] |caps2 = |goals2 = | nationalyears1 = |nationalteam1 = [[El Salvador national under-23 football team|El Salvador U23]] |nationalcaps1 = |nationalgoals1 = | nationalyears2 = 2013 |nationalteam2 = [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]] |nationalcaps2 = 6 |nationalgoals2 = 0 | pcupdate = | ntupdate = }}
{{spanish name 2|Granadino|León}} '''José Miguel Granadino León''' (born September 28, 1988) is a [[El Salvador|Salvadoran]] [[Association football|football]] [[Defender (football)|Defender]] who played for [[C.D. FAS|FAS]].
==Club career== Granadino played has played his entire career for [[C.D. FAS|FAS]].
===Lifeban on match-fixing=== On September 20, 2013, José Miguel Granadino and 13 other players of El Salvador were banned for life, the players were accused of receiving bribes such as a 0-5 defeat against Mexico in 2011 and a 2-4 loss against Paraguay on February 2013. <ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.elgrafico.com/mobile/fourteen-players-banned-for-life-in-match-fixing-case# |title= Fourteen players banned for life in match fixing case |publisher= El Gráfico |accessdate=21 September 2013}}</ref>
