{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Estadio Río Parapití | image = | fullname = Estadio Río Parapití | nickname = Monumental | coordinates = {{coord|22|32|21|S|55|44|44|W|display=title,inline|region:PY_type:landmark_source:dewiki}} | built = | opened = 1999 (after renovation) | seating_capacity = 18,000 | tenants = [[Club 2 de Mayo]] | dimensions = 100 x 66 m }}
'''Monumental Río Parapití''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in the city of [[Pedro Juan Caballero, Paraguay|Pedro Juan Caballero]], [[Paraguay]], used mostly for [[Association football|football]]. It is the home venue of [[Club 2 de Mayo]].
This stadium was used during the 1999 [[Copa América]], hosting games between [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] and [[Peru national football team|Peru]] and between [[Japan national football team|Japan]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].
