{{nihongo|'''Nagano Olympic Stadium'''|長野オリンピックスタジアム|Nagano Orinpikku Sutajiamu}} is a [[baseball]] [[stadium]] in [[Nagano, Nagano]], [[Japan]].  It was used for the opening and closing ceremonies for the [[1998 Winter Olympics]].<ref>[http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1998/Vol2_e.pdf 1998 Winter Olympics official report.] Volume 2. p. 128.</ref>  The stadium holds 35,000 people.

The stadium is the finishing point for the annual [[Nagano Olympic Commemorative Marathon]].<ref>[http://www.naganomarathon.gr.jp/contents/english/12th/course.html Course Route]. Nagano Marathon. Retrieved on 2010-05-01.</ref>

