{{Infobox stadium | name = Pavilhão do Tafe | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Cabinda (city)|Cabinda]], [[Angola]] | coordinates = {{coord|-5.565030|12.190770|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{Start date|2007|08|17}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = State-owned | operator = | surface = Hardwood | scoreboard = Electronic | cost = | architect = SOAPRO | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 2,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = }}
'''Pavilhão do Tafe''' is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Cabinda (city)|Cabinda]], [[Angola]]. The arena, built on the occasion of the [[FIBA Africa Championship 2007|2007 Afrobasket]], alongside the [[Pavilhão Acácias Rubras]] in [[Benguela]], [[Pavilhão Nossa Senhora do Monte|Pavilhão N.Sra do Monte]] in [[Huíla Province|Huíla]] and the [[Pavilhão Serra Van-Dúnem]] in [[Huambo]], has a 2,000-seat capacity.<ref>{{cite web |title=INFRA-ESTRUTURAS DO PAVILHÃO MULTIUSOS DO TAFE |url=http://www.soapro.co.ao/en/portfolio/ampliacao-do-hotel-praia-morena/ |website=SOAPRO |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref>
==See also== * [[Pavilhão Acácias Rubras]] * [[Pavilhão Nossa Senhora do Monte|Pavilhão N.Sra do Monte]] * [[Pavilhão Serra Van-Dúnem]]
