{{infobox country at games | NPC = SLO | NPCname = [[Sports Federation for the Disabled of Slovenia]] | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1992 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.zsis.si }} | location = [[Barcelona]] | competitors = 8 | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = 35 | gold = 2 | silver = 0 | bronze = 1 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1992 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = {{flagIPC|YUG}} (1960–1988) }} '''[[Slovenia]]''' competed at the '''[[1992 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]. 8 competitors from Slovenia won 3 medals including 2 gold and 1 bronze and finished 35th in the [[1992 Summer Paralympics medal table|medal table]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/slovenia|title=Slovenia - National Paralympic Committee|website=www.paralympic.org|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>
